===Etymology===
Tää on ihan hebreaa. Mutta jos osaat tän lukea, olet aika sissi. (tai sit suomalainen)


Terve, Jouni. Onks tää ihan normaalii, ett pääsee editoimaan jotain sivuja?

O.

===Noun===

#The fear of Text.

===Usage===

*"Never say, 'Isorikassikasökösakissakirosi'.  I'm scared of that word; it's too long!"

===Quotations===

*'''2002''' - However, we assume that despite the best endeavours of science, some phobias will always remain. These include [[mitäänsanomattomyydellänsäkään]], or fear of Friday the 13th. And '''hippopotomonstrosesquippedaliophobia''', which is fear of long words.  - anon, ''The Scotsman'' (April 9, 2002) page 13.
*'''2002''' - Those who find this column troubling are suffering from '''hippopotomonstrosesquippedaliophobia''' - the fear of long words. Or, more likely, [[rupophobia]] - a fear of rubbish. - Chris Lloyd in ''The Northern Echo'' (December 14, 2002) page 10

___

In the book ''Useless Knowledge'', this enormous word was misinterpreted by the authors as two words, causing them to list the fear of long words as the following:

:hippopotomonstroses
:and quippedaliophobia

—further distortions of an already very incorrectly formed word (see [[Hippopotomonstrosesquippedaliophobia#Etymology|Etymology]] above!

